    <HorizontalCard
      title="A Paradigm Shift: Innovating Supply Chain Security for AI-Assisted Devices"
      img="/cci_supplychain.png"
      desc="This collaborative project between Old Dominion University (ODU) and Virginia Tech (VT) aims to address the pressing challenges associated with securing supply chains tailored for AI-assisted devices (AADs)." 
      badge="NEW"
      url="https://covacci.org/research/cybersecurity-research"
    />

    <HorizontalCard
      title="T3-CIDERS: A Train-the-Trainer Approach to Fostering CI- and Data-Enabled Research in Cybersecurity"
      img="/NSF_logo.png"
      desc="This collaborative project between Old Dominion University (ODU) and the University of Arizona (UA) aims to develop a unique Trainthe-Trainer Approach to Fostering CyberInfrastructure- and Data-Enabled Research in CyberSecurity (T3- CIDERS). The project will develop technical and pedagogic modules and train future trainers to support effective CI training for large-scale and diverse learners. The T3-CIDERS training will build upon the six CI modules produced by the NSF-funded “DeapSECURE” program, a hands-on introduction to crucial CI technologies directed at cybersecurity research applications."
      badge="NEW"
      url="https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=2320998"
    />
    <HorizontalCard
      title="Spotlighting and Mitigating Cyber‐Attacks in AIoT‐enabled Maritime Transportation"
      img="/maritime_security.jpg"
      desc="This project investigates the cybersecurity implications of an AIoT-enabled MTS (Maritime Transport System), with overarching goals : 1) to evaluate the security effectiveness of AIoT-enabled MTS systems with penetration tests, 2) to tailor new defense models that can counter against cutting-edge cyber-attacks."
      url="https://covacci.org/research/cybersecurity-research/"
      badge="Active"
    />
    <div class="divider my-0"></div>
    <HorizontalCard
    title="Developing a Holistic Evaluation Framework for Multi-Modal AI Security and Trustworthiness on Smart IoT Devices in NextG Wireless Networks"
    img="/iot-security.png"
    desc="This project aims to build a holistic evaluation framework for Multi-Modal AI Security and Trustworthiness on Federated AIoE (AI-enhanced Internet of Everything) with two goals, investigate intrinsically new vulnerabilities and attack vectors in multi-modal AIoE FL systems,  and devise effective algorithms to accurately detect/mitigate the identified attacks."
    url="#"
    badge="Active"

  />
    <div class="divider my-0"></div>
    <HorizontalCard
    title="GPU Powered IoT Testbed to Expand CCI Lab Environment"
    img="/lab_upgrade.jpg"
    desc="This project aims to develop an IoT device testbed inside of the CCI Academic environment with GPU capability.It provides a private cloud environment supporting IoT experimentation and GPU capability for CCI students and faculty greatly benefits both ODU and the region. "
    url="https://covacci.org/cova-share/environments/"
    />

